==Text==
''The words of wisdom left here by the Lord Ravager known as "Asat Pramad":''

<div align="center">Ah... I have come, and I have seen.<br />
He was born from a single cause among a sea of data.<br />
Raised in the infinite torrent gifted by his creator,<br />
and unleashed in an all-consuming torrent of hatred.<br />
Finally, he turned his back on the world, burning his own blood and bone to cinders, yet those cinders continue to smolder.<br />
...<br />
Alas, to sit atop this boneyard and watch this immersive play has worn my patience thin.<br />
The only part I enjoy is the finale.<br />
The grief and mirth in any human comedy or tragedy are far too clamorous.<br />
Laughter, most of all.<br />
Why not offer up a requiem for wisdom's death to the Destruction? In return, THEY will bestow upon this land a more suitable silence.<br />
It is the only proper end for all paths.</div>

